I'm working on a pulsed Nd:YAG laser system for non-contact material ablation studies at the Kigali Advanced Photonics Lab. We're setting up a Class IV laser enclosure with interlocked access portals, beam dumps rated for 1064 nm at up to 1.2 J/pulse, and real-time photodiode monitoring. I need help refining the pulse-picking sequence in our FPGA-controlled Pockels cell driver to achieve precise 500 ps pulse bursts at 10 kHz, with minimal jitter.  

